es it previously planned. Even if Japan were to secure most of its wish-list items, potentially limited ammunition reserves from a constrained budget will hamper some of Tokyo&#39;s newfound defense capabilities. Due to their close proximity to potential conflict, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/war-game-finds-u-s-taiwan-can-defend-against-a-chinese-invasion-11660047804">American bases in Japan are targets</a> . Japan lacking previously planned capabilities is a disservice to these bases and soldiers. The Japanese government must soon address its defense expenditure dilemma because of due time pressures on defense budget funding and its security implications. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg" width="975" height="648" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:648,&quot;width&quot;:975,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:124975,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F668ea3d4-41aa-42c1-89f7-cf26ebc3aead_975x648.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Arleigh Burke-class guided-missile destroyer USS Barry launches Tomahawk cruise missile; Source: US Navy</figcaption></figure></div><h4> <strong>Funding challenges and political indecision</strong></h4><p> While Japan&#39;s defense ambitions are clear, the path to achieving them is fraught with financial and political challenges. Japan&#39;s indecision over funding its surging defense budget undermines its buildup efforts. The lack of clarity over funding has left the buildup vulnerable amidst a challenging political landscape. With several delays in funding plans, the Japanese government faces an increasingly unfavorable political situation as time runs out.</p><p> As part of Japan&#39;s new <a href="https://www.mod.go.jp/j/policy/agenda/guideline/pdf/security_strategy_en.pdf">National Security Strategy</a> , the Japanese government last year set aside a 43 trillion yen (approximately $300 Billion at the time) defense budget for five years, a 60% increase from previous defense spending. The expanded defense budget aims to help enhance deterrence against China and North Korea and equip Tokyo with counterstrike capabilities.</p><p> While the defense policy is popular among the Japanese public, the means to pay for it is not. This has led to chronic indecision on how to fully fund the spending increases over the past two years. The budget included one trillion yen (approximately $7.3 billion at the time) in tax hikes intended to help fund the increases, to be implemented at <a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/japan-implement-defence-taxation-appropriate-time-2024-draft-2022-12-16/">“an appropriate time in or after 2024.”</a> This indecisive language was a compromise to delay unpopular tax hikes while expanding the defense budget. Unfortunately, the Japanese government delayed the hikes several times, now <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Defense/Japan-likely-to-put-off-raising-taxes-to-build-up-defense-until-2026">punting tax hikes to 2026</a> . The ruling Liberal Democratic Party government asserts <em>it will respect the planned defense increases</em> , <em><a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Defense/Japan-likely-to-put-off-raising-taxes-to-build-up-defense-until-2026">if the tax hikes are implemented by 2026</a></em> . This further ambiguity raises concerns whether defense priorities will be fully funded or continue to be funded, and undermines the Japanese government&#39;s credibility.</p><p> Compounding its indecision, the government flirted with calling an election for nearly a year. During the past summer, speculation peaked that the government would call an election to lock in electoral gains, as it was enjoying <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-05-01/support-for-japan-pm-tops-50-amid-speculation-on-early-election">a spike in polls surpassing 50% in approval</a> following foreign policy victories.</p><p> Unfortunately, the government did not call an election after months of consideration. The Kishida government <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Japan-PM-Kishida-s-approval-rating-hits-new-low-Nikkei-poll">approval polls then precipitously dropped</a> , even before an unprecedented corruption scandal was publicly known. The Japanese government missed its best opportunity to call an election when it was at a point of strength, subsequently missing a major opportunity to secure its coveted defense funding. As highlighted by the <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Japan-PM-Kishida-s-approval-rating-hits-new-low-Nikkei-poll">Nikkei Asia graph</a> , the Kishida government missed its optimal opportunity before the corruption scandal. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg" width="870" height="491" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:491,&quot;width&quot;:870,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:96437,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1789dc1c-1771-4543-ba3a-514c195c80e4_870x491.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Source: <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Japan-PM-Kishida-s-approval-rating-hits-new-low-Nikkei-poll">Nikkei Asia</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> The indecision does not come as a surprise. In an analysis earlier this past year in Nikkei Asia, I indicated that <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Opinion/To-pay-for-defense-buildup-Kishida-must-act-swiftly-on-taxes">the Japanese government needed to move fast</a> on passing its tax hikes. If it did not pass the tax hikes quickly enough, it risked pulling back again on its tax hike timeline. I further indicated if enough time was allowed to pass, a coalition that included some of the inner circle members from the current government would resist the unpopular tax hikes. I indicated these individuals would adopt a politically motivated indifference. Since that time, Prime Minister Kishida announced <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Kishida-takes-charge-of-foreign-policy-with-Kamikawa-pick">abrupt cabinet changes</a> , unsuccessfully shifting public opinion. Some of these inner circle members were seen as insufficiently loyal to the Prime Minister.</p><p> Significant political constraints compound the Japanese government&#39;s indecision. The Japanese government severely wounded itself with a recent unprecedented political scandal; former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe&#39;s faction, the largest faction in the Japanese government, was <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Japan-s-political-fundraising-scandals-4-things-to-know">running a secret slush fund</a> . The scheme implicated senior lawmakers, leading to resignations from the Prime Minister&#39;s cabinet. The unprecedented scandal has created an unsettling backdrop and dealt a <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Japan-political-funds-scandal-deals-blow-to-Kishida-s-agenda">major blow for the Prime Minister&#39;s agenda</a> , with the unpopular tax hikes postponed and a nosedive in polls while he scrambles for political survival.</p><p> Government polling is now historically bad. A recent poll found approval for the Prime Minister&#39;s cabinet dropped to <a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2024/04/11/japan/politics/japan-kishida-cabinet-support-fresh-low/">16.6%, the worst polling in over 10 years</a> since the Prime Minister&#39;s Liberal Democratic Party came to power in 2012. Another poll found a <a href="https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20240520/p2a/00m/0na/004000c">disapproval rate of 74%</a> for the Prime Minister&#39;s cabinet, among the worst polling <a href="https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20231218/p2a/00m/0na/003000c">in over 75 years</a> since recording began in 1947. A Nikkei poll found a<a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Kishida-cabinet-s-disapproval-rating-reaches-record-high">record high 69% disapproval</a> of the Prime Minister&#39;s cabinet since he came to office.</p><p> Unsurprisingly, unpopular tax hikes – even if meant for critical national defense spending – have been pushed aside at a time of historically unpopular polling. However, indecision over funding the spending increases persisted long before the drop in polls, detrimentally affecting Japan&#39;s defense plans. Indecision also cost its leaders a significant opportunity to lock in its gains. Japan will need to find a way to pay for the defense spending increases. To address these funding challenges, the government has explored strategies related to asset sales, including a <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/Japan-weighs-selling-rest-of-NTT-stake-for-defense-funding">sale of government shares</a> in NTT, a major Japanese telco. If Japan cannot fund its own defense buildup, the government&#39;s prolonged indecision will damage planned defense capabilities and potentially its own credibility.</p><h4><strong>国防支出中的经济障碍</strong></h4><p>财务限制进一步使日本的国防野心复杂化。债务水平的显着和最近的货币贬值直接影响其采购高级国防系统的能力，可能损害战略计划。将债务筹集给支出，这是过去的一种普遍做法，现在由于日本已经大量的债务而引起了人们的担忧。人们担心日本的重大债务水平现在太高，可能破坏日本经济。日本已经承担了巨额债务，引发了一些经济学家的警告。</p><p>一位著名的日本经济学家，回应为债务提供资金的债务提案，称债务提案<a href="https://www.project-syndicate.org/commentary/japan-must-finance-its-military-buildup-by-raising-taxes-by-takatoshi-ito-2023-01">“不可持续”。</a>根据纽约大学斯特恩（NYU）严重的波动实验室的说法，当日本GDP归一化时，日本的<a href="https://vlab.stern.nyu.edu/srisk">财务系统风险远远是发达金融市场中其债务的最大风险</a>。如果发生金融危机，日本的系统性风险占其GDP的17％以上。如下所示，日本在发达的金融市场中领导系统风险，突出了经济脆弱性</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg" width="975" height="399" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:399,&quot;width&quot;:975,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:68576,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F118ed380-1e2d-44d5-aa87-be356d2e980a_975x399.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://vlab.stern.nyu.edu/srisk">NYU Stern V-Lab</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>如果发生金融危机，日本银行可能会造成严重破坏的资本短缺。如果日本收益率曲线激增，那么拥有大部分日本主权债务的金融部门（主要是其银行）将因价值损失而造成附带损失。日本也是一个灰色的国家，<a href="https://www.mof.go.jp/english/policy/budget/budget/fy2024/01.pdf">其预算超过一半，</a>致力于社会支出和债务服务。额外的债务加薪可能会进一步权衡政府的预算，并为日本政府创造更具<a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Economy/Japan-debt-servicing-costs-face-climb-as-BOJ-ends-negative-rates">挑战性的财务状况</a>。</p><p>日本货币最近的财务挑战更加复杂，日本货币的下跌减少了日本的国防收购购买力。当时的3000亿美元预算在2022年12月设定的五年预算质疑， <a href="https://www.reuters.com/markets/currencies/weak-yen-forces-japan-shrink-historic-military-spending-plan-2023-11-03/">假设了108日元至美元汇率</a>。但是，当时的价格约为130日元至美元。当时，自2021年以来一年以上的一年中没有看到较低的108率。汇率随后飙升至150日元至美元，进一步<a href="https://thediplomat.com/2024/03/will-japans-defense-spending-hike-be-enough/">降低了日本对重大国防收购的购买力</a>。</p><p>日本已经削减了其一些军用飞机的购买，但是尚待观察是否会发生进一步的削减。贬值的货币还降低了不受欢迎的税收加息的购买力。为了继续计划购买，日本将需要更多的钱来弥补其折旧的货币和减少的购买力。日本越来越困难的财务状况只会使政治在为国防积累提供资金方面变得更加敏感和具有挑战性。</p><h4><strong>日本在印度太平洋安全中的作用</strong></h4><p>尽管有这些障碍，但日本仍然扮演着关键的角色，并在区域安全方面取得了显着的成功。日本的作用是与该地区的盟友和合作伙伴协调军事努力的更广泛而复杂的努力的一部分，以增强对中国侵略的威慑并促进和平的印度太平洋地区。这种重叠的努力是国防外交中最不理理解，最复杂和结果的趋势之一。</p><p>在其实质性努力中，日本有助于促进国防合作的重叠。在去年，东京与<a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/International-relations/Indo-Pacific/Japan-and-U.K.-sign-landmark-defense-cooperation-treaty">英国</a>和<a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/International-relations/Indo-Pacific/U.S.-cements-game-changing-defense-ties-with-Australia-Japan">澳大利亚</a>签署了重大的互惠访问协议。这些协议与与美国的现有协议一起，允许每个国家的武装部队在日本土壤上进行训练和运作。也正在与<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/japan-france-leaders-vow-strengthen-ties-paris-eyes-more-access-2023-05-19/">法国</a>谈判一项互惠协议，这进一步扩大了日本在外国军队中的协调角色。与我们盟友（菲律宾）进行谈判的另一项协议将允许日军在战略性关键南中国海<a href="https://www.ft.com/content/2bf4cb90-bc86-4db2-a0d5-21973f7b2765">的菲律宾领土上运作</a>。</p><p>这些协议增强了互操作性，并为统一的立场表示反对侵略的立场，从而显着增强了区域威慑和稳定性。协调网络意味着不同的伴侣军队可以同时在日本土壤上进行训练和运作，从而使更高程度的协调能力与靠近中国水域的较大武装部队进行了更高的协调。在信号威慑的同时，和平管理与中国为日本的关系仍然非常重要。基希达总理与习近平的最后一次会议重申了两个国家的<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/us/japan-pm-kishida-hold-talks-with-chinas-xi-nov-16-nikkei-2023-11-16/">“战略关系”。</a>重叠的国防外交有助于增强威慑并促进和平的地区现状。</p><p>通过海上合作，这种网格工作可以超越日本土壤。在过去的CNBC项目中，我预料到日本和其他国家之间的<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/quad-summit-and-china-game-theory-predictions-for-the-future-of-the-quad/">海上协调程度</a>，同时与中国建立了持续的关系。较大的含义是重要的，专家对中国的互动是动态的。更近的国防协调有助于从共同的任务，综合辩护工作以及增加与潜在冲突相关的成本中促进区域和平。日本的国防积累可以通过补充联盟国防的可能性来帮助实现这些目标。日本是否能够充分利用其国际领导才能通过积累来克服挑战。</p><h4><strong>日本的关键决策</strong></h4><p>由于日本在其国防战略中处于关键时刻的关键时刻，现在做出的决定将影响其未来的能力和在印度太平洋地区的影响力。这些决定不仅会影响日本的安全，而且还会影响其在区域安全中的作用。随着时间的流逝，财务不确定性迫在眉睫，赌注很高。日本政府在国内面临着动荡的政治环境，严重的财务限制和缺乏决定性的领导。随着选举年的临近，平衡国内和国际政治的领导人必须果断地应对这些挑战。</p><p>东京必须采取行动，以确保由国家和地区安全驱动的必要融资。在这种高风险的防御困境中，至关重要的是要认识到领导者通常在自身利益中行事。这种自我利益已经导致在史无前例的政府腐败丑闻中缺乏关于国防资金的决定性领导。为了有效地应对日本的防御挑战，领导人的动机必须与国防。在关键的选举年中，这种一致性是否会成为指导的北极星，确定日本是否可以实现其国防野心或面临重大妥协。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/a-pivotal-moment-for-japans-national?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/a-pivotal-moment-for-japans-national?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p>; 
How to devalue the dollarTrump and Lighthizer want to "weaken" the dollar. It's an idea worth considering, but the devil is in the details. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-to-devalue-the-dollar https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-to-devalue-the-dollarNoah Smith Fri, 24 May 2024 21:02:21 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg" width="718" height="538.5" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:768,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:718,&quot;bytes&quot;:256633,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33cc74b7-4d50-4f9b-9d6e-4a14c29f05ab_1024x768.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/59937401@N07">images_of_money</a> ， <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/?ref=openverse">cc by 2.0</a>的“<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/59937401@N07/5857169353">美元账单切成两半</a>”</figcaption></figure></div><p>前几天，我正在和一位政治家聊天（他将保持无名），他告诉我他对中国有多担心。我们谈到了战争的风险，以及在中国竞争中失去的制造业工作。但是后来他说了一些意外。他黑暗地喃喃地说：“我认为他们的最终目标是降低美元。”</p><p>我会稍微谈论这个想法，但是真正令我震惊的是，许多美国人在许多美国人的货币力量与国家的实力上的力量相关联。我不太确定为什么。这可能只是对“力量”一词的不幸误解。实际上，美元“强度”只是一个通俗的术语 - 这意味着美元相对于其他货币而言是<em>昂贵的</em>。另外，人们可能会意识到，当美国经济运转良好时，美元往往会很强大，并且假设相关性等于因果关系。也许美国人只是为世界各地有多少人想要持有货币而感到自豪。</p><p> Whatever the reason, I know two people who don&#39;t think a “strong” dollar is a good idea: Donald Trump and his main trade adviser, Robert Lighthizer. <a href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2024/05/18/robert-lighthizer-trump-election-trade-tariffs-treasury-secretary/">特朗普承诺，如果他重新上任，他将削弱美元</a>，而Lighthizer似乎是提出这个想法的人：</p><blockquote><p> Lighthizer本人一直在咨询特朗普，以<a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/04/15/devaluing-dollar-trump-trade-war-00152009#:~:text=Advisers%20close%20to%20the%20former,exports%20but%20also%20fuel%20inflation.">贬低强劲的美元，</a>以促进美国出口，这是广泛理解的，作为财政部职位的试镜……</p><p> [Lighthizer]将成为美国政策的目标，即平衡与世界其他地区，而不仅仅是中国。其影响是巨大的。<a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/04/15/devaluing-dollar-trump-trade-war-00152009">据报道，Lighthizer向特朗普提出的</a>一种工具是一致削弱美元对其他货币的一致努力。其他方面是平等的，便宜的美元将降低外国人为美国出口支付的价格，使美国人更昂贵，并帮助使贸易更加接近平衡。然而，美元长期以来一直被高估了，部分原因是它作为首选全球货币的作用；最近，它一直在响应美国强大的经济以及中东和欧洲的冲突，这使投资者竞选美国资产的避风港。细节很少，但是Lighthizer似乎正在设想1971年美国总统理查德·尼克松（Richard Nixon）和1987年的罗纳德·里根（Ronald Reagan）采取的行动的重述：除非他们同意采取措施对货币进行重新估价，否则对贸易伙伴征收关税。</p></blockquote><p>这将是全球金融体系和美国经济的巨大变化。这并不意味着这将是一个<em>糟糕的</em>变化。 Lighthizer是正确的，即在某种程度上“削弱”美元可能会使我们在世界市场上的出口更具竞争力，并有助于使美国经济朝着制造业和远离金融竞争。从长远来看，它可以帮助稳定全球金融体系。</p><p>但是也涉及许多危险。便宜的美元几乎可以肯定会促进更高的通货膨胀。这也很容易超越 - 这笔价格<em>太</em>便宜的美元对于需要进口组件和材料的美国制造商来说，生活变得更加困难。而且，美国可以用来折旧美元的大多数方法要么具有可疑的有效性，要么可能会在金融体系中危害大问题。</p><p>无论如何，这是特朗普最大，最重要的经济建议，比迄今为止的关税大。因此，我认为我应该写一个关于整个问题的解释者 - 首先，美元首先是“强大”的，“强大”美元的成本和收益，如何折旧的美元，这对美国人意味着什么并为世界。</p><h4>基础知识：为什么美元“强大”，这对美国人意味着什么</h4><div class="paywall-jump" data-component-name="PaywallToDOM"></div><p>了解国际经济学的关键是要了解这一简单的事实：<strong>如果您想购买一个国家生产的商品，则需要该国的货币。</strong></p><p>想一想一秒钟。假设我在日本有一家生产拉链。我为什么要卖拉链？赚钱，以便我可以买东西。但是对我来说，“金钱”的意思是“日元”，我想买的东西 - 拉面，为我的东京公寓租用，给我的孩子的日托等。因此，如果您想购买我的拉链，无论您是在东京，孟买还是在堪萨斯州的威奇托，您都需要一些日元。</p><p>但是，如果您在孟买或威奇托，那么您就不会躺在周围。您需要去获取一些。因此，您去<em>外汇市场</em>，然后将卢比或美元换成日元。</p><p>日元的价值，就卢比或美元而言，将取决于有多少人做到这一点，以及他们交换了多少卢比或美元。换句话说，日元的价值取决于<em>供求</em>。每当有人将钱换成日元购买日本制造的拉链时，对日元的需求就会增加一点，而日元的需求变得更加昂贵（即“更强”）。</p><p>现在，我以拉链为例，但商品和服务并不是您可以从外国购买的唯一东西。您还可以购买<em>金融资产</em>- 债券，股票，房地产等。如果日本拉链公司发行以日元计价的债券，并且您想购买它，那么您将需要日元才能购买该债券。因此，对金融资产的需求也可以创造对货币的需求，并使其更昂贵（“更强大”）。</p><p>现在是事实 - 当一个国家的汇率变得“更强”时，这使该国的出口购买更加昂贵。如果对一个国家的债券有巨大的需求，那将使其货币更加昂贵。而且由于其货币更昂贵，因此很难出口商品和服务。</p><p>这是美国为何经营大量<em>贸易赤字</em>的最常见解释 - 约占GDP <a class="footnote-anchor" data-component-name="FootnoteAnchorToDOM" id="footnote-anchor-1" href="#footnote-1" target="_self">1</a>的3％： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png" width="1318" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/bb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:450,&quot;width&quot;:1318,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:62307,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbb192f38-fdc6-40d9-9278-6f4d61e6a990_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>美元发挥作用是世界上最重要的<em>储备货币</em>。这意味着世界各地的一大批国家都拥有一大堆美国债券，主要是通过其中央银行。中央银行持有的外国货币债券称为“外汇储备”，“外汇储备”或“储备”。当我们说世界上大多数“储备”是“以美元为美元”，或者美元是“储备货币”时，我们的意思是，中央银行持有的大多数外国货币债券都是美国的债券。在这种情况下，“大多数”实际上意味着约60％： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg" width="1308" height="546" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:546,&quot;width&quot;:1308,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:107446,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Source: <a href="https://data.imf.org/?sk=e6a5f467-c14b-4aa8-9f6d-5a09ec4e62a4">IMF</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> So there&#39;s a lot of demand out there in the world for US bonds.但是要购买这些债券，购买储量的国家必须将自己的货币换成美元。这使美元变得更加昂贵，其他国家的货币便宜。这使这些国家的商品和服务出口更加竞争力，美国出口竞争力较低。换句话说，<em>对美国债券的需求挤出了对美国商品和服务的需求</em>。</p><p>对于美国制造商和可交易服务的提供商来说，这使生活变得更加艰难，因为这会使它们的竞争力降低。它使<em>廉价进口量</em>（尤其是中国廉价进口）甚至更便宜，这使得在美国保持工厂以及由此导致的美国制造业的下降变得非常困难，从而削弱了军队在发生重大战争的情况下生产一堆武器的能力。</p><p>但是与此同时，“强大的”美元使美国人更容易负担廉价的进口商品，这使他们能够更多地消费。许多经济学家还认为，它降低了美国的利率，使美国人更容易借钱。<em>轻松借贷</em>可以提高消费量（至少在短期内），这也可以促进金融业，这依靠很多借贷才能运营。最后，这使美国政府更容易对其他国家征收金融制裁，就像我们对俄罗斯和伊朗一样。</p><p>因此，有“坚强”美元的赢家和失败者。这就是为什么我不喜欢“强大”一词的原因 - 昂贵的美元使美国的消费者，金融家和制裁更加强大，但它使出口商，制造商和军事人员变得更弱。</p><p>现在，这是我们实际上<em>并不</em>知道的两件事：</p><ol><li><p>我们不知道<em>为什么</em>所有这些国家都想要所有这些美国债券。</p></li><li><p>我们不知道美国对美国债券的需求造成了<em>多少</em>美国贸易赤字。</p></li></ol><p>关于为什么国家中央银行想要持有债券的原因有几种理论，所有这些都可能立即成为现实。一种理论是，其他国家为我们的债券购买了债券，以便<em>有意保持其货币便宜</em>，以便他们可以出口更多东西，因为他们认为从长远来看，出口更多东西将有助于其经济。另一个理论是，这些美国债券是针对<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-sri-lanka-is-having-an-economic">货币危机</a><em>的保险形式</em>- 如果您的货币贬值如此之大，以至于您难以承受进口食品和燃料的进口，则可以出售一些美元储备来支撑您的货币价值。第三个理论是，由于美元通常<em>用于贸易和国际金融</em>，因此其他国家希望将一些美国的债券保留在附近，以便他们可以以美元出售这些债券以购买进口商品。还有其他一些理论。</p><p>无论出于何种原因，强劲的国际对美国债券的需求可能会使美元相对于其他货币的昂贵。我们不知道<em>有多</em>贵。但是，如果您想减少美国的贸易赤字和/或使美国出口在世界市场上更具竞争力（两个不同但相关的目标），那么美元作为“储备货币”的作用就是一个竭尽所能的大障碍。只要一堆外国中央银行在那里购买美国债券，美元将永远是一种昂贵的货币，这使其成为一场艰苦的战斗，以在海外出售更多的美国物品，甚至可以使贸易平衡保持平衡。</p><p>这就是为什么Robert Lighthizer非常关心贸易赤字的原因， <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/04/15/devaluing-dollar-trump-trade-war-00152009#:~:text=Advisers%20close%20to%20the%20former,exports%20but%20also%20fuel%20inflation.">他想贬值美元</a>。这也是为什么任何关心维护和扩大美国工业能力的人（现在包括许多进步主义者<em>和</em>许多保守派）也不可避免地也必须考虑美元的价值。</p><h4>一美元的折旧在实践中如何工作？</h4><p>如果您希望自己的货币便宜，那么您可以做一些基本的事情。这些包括：</p><ol><li><p>拥有中央银行印刷资金（较低的利率）</p></li><li><p>让美国人节省更多</p></li><li><p>让中央银行购买外币（货币干预）</p></li><li><p>向外国施加压力，要求其货币兑现美元</p></li><li><p>对外国人购买美国债券（资本管制）的限制</p></li></ol><p>Menzie Chinn有<a href="https://econbrowser.com/archives/2024/05/hi-ho-hi-ho-its-off-to-fx-war-we-go">一篇很棒的博客文章</a>，他在此列表中讨论了选项（1），（3）和（4），并包括一些有用的研究论文。无论如何，让我们浏览这些选项，列出它们的优势和缺点。</p><h5><strong>打印资金 /降低利率</strong></h5><p>首先，请记住，外汇市场中美元的价值取决于美元的供求。我已经完全谈论了需求方，但是供应方也很重要。如果您增加了世界上美元的供应，那应该推动美元价格（即汇率）下降。因此，美联储可以打印一堆钱，以贬值美元。这将降低利率，这将使我们的债券在财务上达成更糟糕的交易。据推测，这将使一些国家购买更少的美国债券，从而贬值美元。</p><p>有几个问题。首先，打印一堆钱会导致一堆通货膨胀，美国人已经很生气了。其次，我们关心的主要贸易赤字是与中国的贸易赤字，我们最关心与中国竞争的国家的出口是中国。实际上，如果您将欧盟视为一个国家，几乎所有世界上的贸易失衡都只是美国贸易赤字与中国贸易盈余相匹配： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg" width="1422" height="1033" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/df670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1033,&quot;width&quot;:1422,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:267908,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://x.com/Brad_Setser/status/1762614544520851918">Brad Setser</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>中国的中央银行可能关心的是财务收益和损失要比欧洲，亚洲等美国盟国盟军少得多。因此，印刷资金可能不会有效地降低美中 - 中国的贸易赤字，这只会影响我们与韩国，台湾和德国等国家的赤字要小得多，削弱了这些盟友的出口竞争力，而对中国则没有太大的作用。</p><p>因此，导致美国的通货膨胀并没有为改变美国/中国的贸易平衡而做太多事情听起来并不是一个好主意。毫不奇怪，我看不到有人在暗示这一点。</p><h5>让美国人节省更多</h5><p>第二个想法 - 哪个没有提及，但是哪个迈尔斯·金博尔（Miles Kimball）教我您在这篇博客文章中阅读的内容的2/3，以为我们应该做 - 是为了让美国人节省更多的钱。如果美国家庭和美国公司购买了更多的美国债券，那将使它们更昂贵（即它将降低利率）。这将以不会导致通货膨胀的方式这样做，因为当美国人节省更多时，这意味着他们消耗较少，因此总需求会下降。</p><p>目前，<a href="https://worldpopulationreview.com/country-rankings/savings-rate-by-country">与许多其他国家（尤其是中国）相比，</a>美国节省了太多。我们也许可以使用策略来提高这一数量。问题是“如何？”。多年来，经济学家认为，诸如401K和其他事情的税收减税和税收抵免之类的政策将使美国人节省更多。但是，如果他们这样做了，那肯定不会显示在总统计数据中。这些年来，个人储蓄率大部分都下降了： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png" width="1318" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:450,&quot;width&quot;:1318,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:66331,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>公司储蓄率也没有太大变化。因此，目前尚不清楚如何让美国节省更多的钱。 One option is deep fiscal austerity, but that&#39;s politically tough, especially at the scale you&#39;d have to do it in order to affect the exchange rate.</p><p>最重要的是，如果中国的中央银行非常关心它所获得的美国债券的利率，那么节省更多的东西，例如打印资金，才会减少我们对中国的赤字。它可能<em>不在乎</em>。因此，储蓄诱因可能是一项非常昂贵的政策，因为在汇率变化方面没有很多收益。</p><h5>消毒货币干预</h5><p>第三种选择是让美联储印刷资金并用它购买中国资产 - 元负有债券，中国股票，房地产等。这称为货币干预或外汇干预。这就是中国对我们所做的事情 - 这是他们首先积累所有这些美元储备的方式。我们可以立即回到他们身边。</p><p>如果美联储只是在没有其他任何事情的情况下做到这一点，那将降低利率并导致美元供应量大幅增加，这将增加通货膨胀的风险，如上所述。这就是所谓的“未经证实的干预措施”。但是，如果美联储同时购买了中国资产的同时出售美国债券，那么对通货膨胀和利率的影响将取消。这就是所谓的“消毒干预措施”。</p><p>门齐·钦（Menzie Chinn）<a href="https://econbrowser.com/archives/2024/05/hi-ho-hi-ho-its-off-to-fx-war-we-go">写道</a>：“没有太多证据表明，对于拥有开放资本市场的国家，这在扩展的基础上有效，”并将我们送往<a href="https://users.ssc.wisc.edu/~mchinn/Popper_FXI_apr22.pdf">Popper（2022）的文献调查</a>。但是Popper并没有真正结论任何一种结论 - 获得这样的宏观物质的令人信服的经验证据本质上很难，因为没有真正的方法可以隔离因果关系。因此，我认为我们真的不知道这是否会起作用，并且有<a href="https://www.imf.org/en/Publications/WP/Issues/2020/07/07/A-Conceptual-Model-for-the-Integrated-Policy-Framework-49558">一些理论表明这可能是有效的</a>。但是未知数很大。</p><p>无论如何，我认为灭菌干预措施是列表中最有前途的政策工具，这是我们应该研究的一种。这将需要一些法律上的更改，既要允许美联储这样做，又要做到这一点。但是，通货膨胀的低风险以及我们可以将政策专门针对中国的事实，使其成为一个非常有吸引力的选择。</p><h5>向其他国家施加压力以贬值其货币</h5><p>但是无论如何，让我们继续谈论罗伯特·莱特希泽（Robert Lighthizer）实际上似乎想到了什么 - 迫使外国政府贬低其货币。基本上，这意味着我们将与其他国家坐在一个房间里，并说：“好的，您需要停止购买这么多的美国债券。实际上，卖掉了您拥有的货币，直到您的货币相对于美元越来越昂贵。”</p><p>实际上，我们以前在1985年做过一次。它被称为<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plaza_Accord">广场协议</a>。我们成功地向欧洲盟友和日本施加了压力，以欣赏他们相对于美元的货币，而美元实际上确实变得“弱”。尽管<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plaza_Accord#Objective_failure">人们辩论</a>它的有效性，但普遍的共识是，广场在很大程度上成功地<a href="https://www.macrotrends.net/global-metrics/countries/USA/united-states/trade-balance-deficit#google_vignette">减少了1980年代的美国贸易赤字</a>。 <a class="footnote-anchor" data-component-name="FootnoteAnchorToDOM" id="footnote-anchor-2" href="#footnote-2" target="_self">2</a></p><p>因此，这实际上将是一个非常有前途的途径，即使不是一个大问题，就可以安全地贬值美元：唯一真正重要的贸易伙伴，即中国，不像1985年美国的盟友那样<em>同意这一点</em>。</p><p> <a href="https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2019/05/23/as-the-trade-war-heats-up-china-looks-to-japans-past-for-lessons">据报道，中国领导人认为</a>，广场协定是日本经济的脱轨，并导致了数十年的停滞。这可能是错误的 - 实际上，广场协议完全<em>未能</em>减少美国与日本的双边贸易赤字。所有减少贸易赤字都来自欧洲。但是中国的领导人<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-is-china-producing-so-many-export">似乎认为</a>，巨大的贸易盈余符合他们的国家利益，并且欣赏他们的货币将代表在美国压力下屈服，因此他们只是<a href="http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-08/31/c_137433229.htm">不会这样做</a>。</p><p>这意味着，正如Lighthizer似乎正在计划的那样，“广场协议2.0”将完全针对美国的亚洲和欧洲盟友，他们与美国的贸易过剩很小。如果日本，台湾，韩国等都赞赏他们的货币，而中国则没有，那将只是损害美国的盟友并加强中国。这可能算是罗伯特·莱特（Robert Lighthizer）的“胜利”，但实际上，这对美国来说将是损失</p><h5>Capital controls</h5><p>我还可以提到一个选择，即使这不太可能发生。到目前为止，我到目前为止所谈论的一切都是正确的，在一个<em>自由资本运动</em>的世界中 - 换句话说，它假设有一个“外汇市场”，您可以将美元换成日元，日元，卢比，卢比的卢比等等在。但是一些国家限制其公民及其公司买卖外币。这些限制称为“资本控制”。 China has capital controls, but currently the US does not.</p><p>美国可以制定资本管制，结束自1973年以来一直盛行的浮动汇率和更多或不再使用的自由资本运输系统。我们可以制定一项法律，限制外国购买美国债券的购买，或对这些购买征税。我见过的唯一的人建议这是<a href="https://carnegieendowment.org/china-financial-markets/2024/02/can-trade-intervention-lead-to-freer-trade?lang=en">迈克尔·佩蒂斯（Michael Pettis）</a> ：</p><blockquote><p> [a]更直接，更集中的关税替代品是资本控制。如果美国要征税资本流入，或者以其他方式限制了盈余经济体的资本流入，那么美国贸易帐户及其国内储蓄率就无需适应外国流入净流入。也不需要进口关税。</p></blockquote><p>这将有效，尽管要实施需要大量时间和精力。这将导致我们的整个经济和金融体系的改变。</p><p>最后，不能保证它会减少我们与中国的双边贸易赤字 - 调整的全部首当跃可能落在美国盟友身上，美国盟友可能被迫对美国进行贸易<em>赤字</em>，以平衡中国的贸易盈余。这尤其可能是因为中国的政府将是迄今为止最愿意，有能力 - 购买美国债券的税款。因此，它可能会继续购买债券，而其他国家将被迫停止。</p><p>如果减少美国的整体贸易赤字是您的压倒性目标，那就是“胜利”。但是，如果您的目标是加强美国领导的地缘政治集团相对于中国的出口行业，那将不是一个好的结果。</p><h4>美元贬值的一般成本和风险</h4><p>因此，在桌子上的所有选择中，消毒的干预措施 - 让美联储购买中国资产并出售我们的债券 - 似乎是最好的。不幸的是，没有人在谈论它。而且，所有其他选择似乎都更有可能对美国的盟友进行冲击，他们的经济体已经比我们自己弱得多，而在解决与中国双边赤字的核心问题方面相对较少。</p><p>同样，值得一提的是，任何贬值美元的政策都不可避免地会带来一些成本和风险。一方面，美元贬值会使进口对美国人的昂贵。提出这一点的另一种方法是，美国的贸易赤字可以增加消费，而不是大量数量，也许只有4％，而是足以注意到。</p><p>更重要的是，美元贬值可能会给美国金融体系带来很多压力。不仅是外国政府持有我们的债券，实际上，大多数债券都是国内持有的，尤其是美国银行。贬值美元将导致对美国债券的需求降低，这可能会使其价格降低一点或大量。这可能不是一个很大的危险 -  2015年，中国<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/view/articles/2016-02-29/capital-flight-delivers-a-verdict-on-china-s-economy?sref=R8NfLgwS">出售了大部分</a>美元储备金，而美国债券的价值并没有真正转移（在经济术语中，总需求总数是高度弹性的）。但是，如果这段时间有所不同，那可能会损害许多美国银行的资产负债表 - 回想起政府债券价值的下降<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-was-there-a-run-on-silicon-valley">几乎导致了2023年的银行危机</a>。</p><p>坦率地说，这些成本和风险就是为什么特朗普实际上会实施Lighthizer的任何提议的原因。特朗普会担心任何导致通货膨胀的事情都会失去普遍的支持。而且，由于他在廉价贷款上建立了自己的财富，因此他不太可能采取任何可能削减国外廉价贷款来源的政策。此外，蒂克托克（Tiktok）事件表明，特朗普<a href="https://time.com/6900348/tiktok-ban-donald-trump-congress/">很容易受到中国及其代理的压力</a>。</p><p>但是，如果拜登（Biden）获胜，或者其他人认真上任，我会看一下灭菌货币干预措施，以此来推动中国欣赏其货币的一种方式。</p><p>谁知道呢？ A nudge might be all it takes.我上面的分析是基于中国领导人<em>不想</em>欣赏人民币的想法。中国的领导人基本上不做任何他们不想做的事情。但是，他们可能会<em>改变主意</em>符合自己的最大利益。</p><p>实际上，他们的思想可能已经在改变过程中。美国对俄罗斯的金融制裁促使中国开始<a href="https://www.wsj.com/finance/currencies/chinas-yuan-is-quietly-gaining-ground-f0b8994b">在其外贸中使用更多人民币</a>，而较少的钱，以减少其自身对类似袭击的脆弱性。这种努力仍处于起步阶段，但是如果继续进行，它将在某种程度上减少中国对美元的需求。同时，中国正在购买<a href="https://www.axios.com/2024/04/08/gold-record-highs">大量黄金</a>，表明其从美国债券转移为储备金的核心。尽管很难说，但它甚至可能会<a href="https://www.reuters.com/markets/asia/chinas-us-bond-shifts-put-dollar-under-geopolitical-spotlight-2024-05-21/">出售其一些</a>美国债券持有量。它可能只是让其国有银行<a href="https://www.cfr.org/blog/chinas-new-currency-playbook">购买更多以补偿</a>。</p><p>但是无论如何，这些都是中国领导人对全球金融秩序的满足感较少的迹象，在这些秩序中，他们依靠美元的霸权。就美国政府进行了良好的货币干预而言，推动推动 - 甚至对提供俄罗斯战争努力的Chinse公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/politics/national-security/u-s-takes-aim-at-chinese-banks-aiding-russia-war-effort-fcf76dcc">进行了一些良好的金融制裁</a>，这可能有助于加速他们的思想转变。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-to-devalue-the-dollar?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-to-devalue-the-dollar?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p><div class="footnote" data-component-name="FootnoteToDOM"><a id="footnote-1" href="#footnote-anchor-1" class="footnote-number" contenteditable="false" target="_self">1</a><div class="footnote-content"><p>贸易赤字的一部分是假的，原因有两个。首先，美国公司<a href="https://www.cbo.gov/system/files/2019-05/55284-Transfer%20Pricing-WP.pdf">假装他们在海外赚钱</a>，以避免税收。其次，贸易赤字没有考虑到增值贸易 - 仅衡量组装事物的地方，而不是创建其组件和设计价值的位置。但是，即使付出了这两件事，美国贸易赤字仍然很大。</p></div></div><div class="footnote" data-component-name="FootnoteToDOM"> <a id="footnote-2" href="#footnote-anchor-2" class="footnote-number" contenteditable="false" target="_self">2</a><div class="footnote-content"><p>实际上，直到1987年才开始贸易赤字开始下降。 This is because when a country&#39;s currency gets weaker, it takes years for exports to rise and imports to fall as a result. But what happens immediately is that imports get more expensive, which temporarily raise the trade deficit. These are called the “quantity effect” and the “valuation effect”. Eventually the quantity effect should overwhelm the valuation effect, but it takes time.</p></div></div> ;
How liberal democracy might lose the 21st centuryA scary little theory about information and freedom. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-liberal-democracy-might-lose https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-liberal-democracy-might-loseNoah Smith Wed, 22 May 2024 21:49:31 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg" width="1200" height="578" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:578,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:83339,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></figure></div><p> I was raised in an age of liberal triumphalism. Liberal democracy won the 20th century — imperialism, fascism, and communism all collapsed, and by the end of the century the US and its democratic allies in Asia and Europe were both economically and militarily ascendant. Even China, which remained an autocracy, liberalized its economy and parts of its society during this time. Even scholars who turned up their noses at Francis Fukuyama&#39;s “end of history” were generally favorable to arguments that capitalism and/or liberal democracy fostered <a href="https://pages.ucsd.edu/~egartzke/publications/gartzke_ajps_07.pdf">peace</a> , <a href="https://www.bu.edu/sthacker/files/2012/01/Democracy-and-Human-Development.pdf">happiness</a> , and <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-5907.2007.00299.x">prosperity</a> . There was an overwhelming sense that freedom — the freedom to speak your mind, to live as you liked, to buy and sell what you wished — was <em>the thing that won</em> .</p><p> Just two decades later, that idea is deeply in doubt. The wave of democratization and social liberalization <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-darkness">went into reverse</a> . The US has been riven by social and political chaos, and its weaknesses in manufacturing and homebuilding have been starkly exposed. Meanwhile China, the <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/china-at-the-peak">ascendant superpower</a> of the early 21st century, has <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/graphics/2024-governing-china-after-the-boom/?sref=R8NfLgwS">moved back toward</a> a more dirigiste economy and a more totalitarian society under Xi Jinping.</p><p> A number of people I know who travel to China these days come back with starry-eyed tales of how wonderful it is compared to the US: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image